h1. userLoggedIn

Event broadcast on the [$rootScope|http://docs.angularjs.org/api/ng/service/$rootScope] when
 user logs in using [security|Angular Services]. The newly logged in user is passed as the event's argument.

h2. Usage
Register the handler on the current scope or the [$rootScope|http://docs.angularjs.org/api/ng/service/$rootScope]
to listen to user login events.


{code}
$scope.$on('userLoggedIn', function(event, user) {
    // show more content
})
{code}
